24/07/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Commander of NATO headquarters in Sarajevo, Major General Richard Whitman, met on Monday (July 23rd) with Republika Srprksa (RS) Interior Minister Stanislav Cado and with Jovan Spaic, chairman of the working group, tasked with implementing RS's action plan for war crimes co-operation. Whitman reiterated NATO's willingness to assist RS in meeting its commitments to the UN war crimes tribunal at The Hague, including the arrest of remaining fugitives. He also praised the work of RS security agencies in the past year. (Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni Avaz - 24/07/07; RTRS, Fena - 23/07/07)
